---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BuyCta from '../../../components/BuyCta.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema, productReviewSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'Einhell GE-EM 1233 M Review - Budget Electric That Actually Works (2026)';
const description = "Einhell GE-EM 1233 M corded electric mower review. 33cm deck, 1250W motor, £139 - research-led verdict on the cheapest mower worth buying.";
const path = '/reviews/einhell-review/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Electric lawn mowers', url: '/electric-lawn-mowers/' },
  { name: 'Einhell GE-EM 1233 M review', url: path },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the Einhell GE-EM 1233 M any good?', a: 'For the money, yes. It\'s a basic corded electric mower that cuts grass reliably on small lawns up to 200 m². Don\'t expect premium build quality or fancy features - but at £139 it does exactly what it\'s supposed to do without breaking.' },
  { q: 'What size lawn is the Einhell 1233 good for?', a: 'Up to 200 m² comfortably. The 33 cm deck and corded design mean you\'ll be managing a cable, so anything over 200 m² becomes tedious. For larger lawns, go cordless.' },
  { q: 'Is the Einhell 1233 self-propelled?', a: 'No - it\'s push-only. At 10 kg it\'s light enough that self-propulsion isn\'t needed on flat ground. On slopes you\'ll feel the effort more than with a self-propelled model.' },
  { q: 'Einhell vs Flymo Easimo - which budget mower is better?', a: 'Both are sub-£150 corded electrics for small gardens. The Einhell has a grass box (30L) and wheeled design - better for conventional mowing. The Flymo Easimo is a hover mower - better for uneven ground and awkward shapes. Choose based on your lawn terrain.' },
  { q: 'How long is the cable on the Einhell 1233?', a: 'It doesn\'t include a cable - you need your own extension lead. We recommend a 25 m outdoor-rated cable reel (about £25-£35) which covers most small gardens comfortably.' },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished, dateModified: '2026-06-05' }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
  productReviewSchema({ name: 'Einhell GE-EM 1233 M', brand: 'Einhell', description, rating: 4.0, url: path, datePublished, dateModified: '2026-06-05', image: '/images/einhell_corded_electric_mower.webp', priceLow: 110, priceHigh: 170, reviewBody: 'The cheapest mower we recommend without caveat. Basic, reliable, does the job on small UK lawns under 200 m². Nothing fancy - just honest cutting.' }),
];
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} {schema}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Research-led review · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">Einhell GE-EM 1233 M Review</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-500 text-sm">By The Best Mowers UK · Research-led assessment from specs and verified owner reviews</p>
    </header>

    <aside class="bg-grass-50 border-l-4 border-grass-700 rounded-r-lg p-5 mb-10">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Our verdict</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-soil-900">4.0 / 5</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-right text-sm">
          <p class="font-semibold text-soil-900">£139 RRP</p>
          <p class="text-slate-500">Best budget corded electric</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        The Einhell GE-EM 1233 M is the cheapest mower we recommend without caveat. It doesn't pretend to be anything it isn't - a basic, lightweight, corded electric mower for small UK gardens. The 1250W motor handles typical British grass without stalling, the 30L box collects adequately, and verified owner reviews report years of trouble-free weekly use. For £139, that's all you need.
      </p>
          <BuyCta name="Einhell GE-EM 1233 M" rrp="£139" />
    </aside>

    <img src="/images/einhell_corded_electric_mower.webp" alt="Einhell corded electric lawn mower on a small UK lawn" width="900" height="506" class="w-full rounded-xl my-6 object-cover" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" />

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>Specs</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Cutting width</th><td>33 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Motor</th><td>1250W electric</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Power source</th><td>Corded (extension lead required)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Weight</th><td>10 kg</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Cut heights</th><td>5 positions, 20-60 mm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Grass box</th><td>30 litres</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Mulching</th><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Self-propelled</th><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Deck material</th><td>Polypropylene</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Warranty</th><td>2 years</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>What owners praise</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The price</strong> - £139 for a functioning, reliable mower from a known brand. Hard to argue with.</li>
        <li><strong>Light as anything</strong> - 10 kg means anyone can push it, lift it, store it on a hook. No strain whatsoever.</li>
        <li><strong>Simple</strong> - plug in, squeeze the bail, mow. No batteries to charge, no fuel to mix, no app to configure. It just works.</li>
        <li><strong>Adequate cut quality</strong> - not competition-grade, but perfectly tidy on a typical small UK lawn mowed weekly.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The drawbacks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The cable</strong> - you'll spend 20% of your mow managing an extension lead. It's the eternal downside of corded electric mowers.</li>
        <li><strong>30L box fills fast</strong> - on anything longer than 50 mm cutting height, expect 3-4 empties on a 150 m² lawn.</li>
        <li><strong>Plastic deck</strong> - functional but you can feel the cost saving. Won't survive being dropped onto concrete.</li>
        <li><strong>No mulching</strong> - collect only. If you want to skip the box, you'll need a mulch plug model (not available on this unit).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How it compares</h2>
      <p>
        The closest rival is the <a href="/reviews/flymo-easimo-review/">Flymo Easimo</a> at £89 - cheaper but it's a hover mower (no wheels, no grass box as standard). The <a href="/reviews/mountfield-princess-34/">Mountfield Princess 34</a> at £249 is the step-up if you want a rear roller for stripes. For first-time buyers on a tight budget who just want a basic wheeled mower that works, the Einhell is the sensible choice.
      </p>

      <h2>Who should buy it</h2>
      <p>
        First-time homeowners or renters with small gardens (under 200 m²) who want a basic, reliable mower without spending more than necessary. Students, first-flat buyers, anyone who needs a mower but doesn't care about bells and whistles.
      </p>
      <p>
        Don't buy it if your lawn is over 200 m² (cable management becomes painful), if you want cordless freedom (Gtech CLM at £249), or if you need mulching capability.
      </p>
    </div>

    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
